                  <td width="560" valign="top" bgcolor="#C4EECE" class="style2"><p class="style79"><strong><em>Twists and turns on a  long march:&nbsp; </em></strong><em>The road forward for standards in China continues to  twist and turn, with sometimes conflicting official statements and Western  fears of ongoing use by China of home-grown standards to provide advantages to  domestic vendors and service providers.&nbsp;  But there has also been&nbsp; progress  in other areas of standards development.&nbsp;  Meanwhile, the efforts of global standards organizations to involve  Chinese participation continue, as with the decision of the W3C to open an  office in Beijing in order to encourage Chinese collaboration in developing &ndash;  and using &ndash; global Internet and Web standards.</em></p></td>
